('PHIL231','Environmental and Animal Ethics', 'PHIL', 4, 'P1067', 'TR 10:30-12:00', 'C103', 30, 'This course will examine the ethical dimensions of our relationship to non-human animals and the environment, including a special emphasis on climate justice as the site of interconnected and global moral, political, and scientific concerns. Some of the questions we will address include: What is the relation between the environment and human health and well-being?'),
